{
  "title": "Integer limits should stay within IEEE-754 safe range",
  "description": "Languages that use IEEE-754 doubles (e.g. JavaScript) can only represent integers accurately between âˆ’9 007 199 254 740 991 and +9 007 199 254 740 991. Declare `minimum`/`maximum` inside that range to avoid precision loss.",
